data.title: Inside Joe Jonas' Show Ready Routine
data.meta_description: Produced by Vogue with Xeomin (incobotulinumtoxinA) | The Jonas Brothers and DNCE frontman walks us through pre-show routines as he discusses what he loves about touring, the lessons he’s learned from being on movie sets, and why his bags are always packed.Please see Additional Consumer Safety Information at End of VideoXeomin is a temporary treatment.XEOMIN® (incobotulinumtoxinA) IMPORTANT CONSUMER SAFETY INFORMATIONRead the Medication Guide before you start receiving XEOMIN (Zeo-min) and each time XEOMIN is given to you as there may be new information. The risk information provided here is not comprehensive. To learn more:• Talk to your health care provider or pharmacist• Visit www.xeominaesthetic.com to obtain the FDA-approved product labelingCall 1-866-862-1211UsesXEOMIN is a prescription medicine that is injected into muscles and used to improve the look of moderate to severe frown lines between the eyebrows (glabellar lines) in adults for a short period of time (temporary).WarningsXEOMIN may cause serious side effects that can be life threatening. Call your doctor or get medical help right away if you have any of these problems anytime (hours to weeks) after treatment with XEOMIN:• Problems with swallowing, speaking, or breathing can happen within hours to weeks after an injection of XEOMIN if the muscles that you use to breathe and swallow become weak. Death can happen as a complication if you have severe problems with swallowing or breathing after treatment with XEOMIN.• Spread of toxin effects. In some cases, the effect of botulinum toxin may affect areas of the body away from the injection site and cause symptoms of a serious condition called botulism. The symptoms of botulism include: loss of strength and muscle weakness all over the body, double vision, blurred vision and drooping eyelids, hoarseness or change or loss of voice, trouble saying words clearly, loss of bladder control, trouble breathing, trouble swallowing.These symptoms can happen hours to weeks after you receive an injection of XEOMIN. These problems could make it unsafe for you to drive a car or do other dangerous activities.Do not use XEOMIN if you are allergic to XEOMIN or any of the ingredients in XEOMIN (see the end of this Guide for a list of ingredients in XEOMIN), had an allergic reaction to any other botulinum toxin products or have a skin infection at the planned injection site.Before receiving XEOMIN, tell your doctor about all of your medical conditions.Tell your doctor about all of the medicines you take, including prescription and over-the-counter medicines, vitamins and herbal supplements. Talk to your doctor before you take any new medicines after you receive XEOMIN.¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬¬Possible Side EffectsXEOMIN can cause serious side effects that can be life threatening including allergic reactions. Symptoms of an allergic reaction to XEOMIN may include: itching, rash, redness, swelling, wheezing, asthma symptoms, or dizziness or feeling faint. Tell your doctor or get medical help right away if you get wheezing or asthma symptoms, or if you get dizzy or faint. See “Warnings.”The most common side effect of XEOMIN in people with glabellar lines include:• headacheThese are not all the possible side effects of XEOMIN. Call your doctor for medical advice about side effects. You may report side effects to FDA at 1-800-FDA-1088.Intended for U.S. audiences.

Hey, Vogue, I have a magic door.

Oh, no, lemme start again.

[video beeping]

[clapperboard banging]

Hey Vogue, what's up?

Joe Jonas here.

We've got a show tonight

and I wanna take you through my routine before the big gig.

So come on in.

[gentle instrumental music]

I'm on the road quite a bit,

whether if it's actually touring, on a film project,

my bags are always packed.

Music is everything to me,

performing and traveling is definitely

one of my favorite parts.

I'm so grateful that I get to call this my gig.

It's definitely important

for me to have a routine that I follow.

As long as I have this,

I feel like I can perform to the best of my ability.

The first thing I do is meditate,

but I'll do about 3 to 10 minute meditation,

sometimes even when I'm brushing my teeth on the go.

I like to do a gratitude list,

whether I jot in my phone

or I actually write 'em down in a journal, pen to paper.

If I exercise, I feel great,

whether it's just a simple walk.

They don't tell you when you book movies

that you're gonna be sitting around a lot.

So wherever I was, I built this like 20,

30 minute workout.

It's just about being able to feel good,

especially on stage.

So since I have a show later,

I'm gonna start off with a shave.

Alright.

I'm gonna be using this beard trimmer

and gonna take some of this scruff down.

[beard trimmer whirring]

My routine has changed quite a bit

because I didn't have as much facial hair.

Growing up, my dad was the first one

to teach me how to properly shave.

And I think it was from that little mustache

that appeared in middle school.

So one little secret is I like to bag all of my facial hair

and sell it online.

[beard trimmer whirring]

I'm joking.

[beard trimmer whirring]

[water splashing]

So the next step, time to shave.

It's been a minute, so I'm a bit outta practice.

About a year ago,

I was in a film that I played a naval officer.

So every day I'm out there,

clean faced, combed back hair.

And so I started getting into routine shaving every day.

And the routine, I really liked it,

I looked forward to it.

But I think, Vouge,

you might have my wife a little upset

with you because she likes the scruff.

But it's alrighty, it grows back quick.

[gentle instrumental music]

Alright, next step is the face wash.

Touring can definitely take a toll on your skin.

I mean, you're traveling constantly.

I definitely feel great on stage

when I know I've spent the time to take care of myself.

So I hit that stage feeling really confident.

So I was talking to my dermatologist

about my skincare routine

where they suggested I get treated with a smart toxin

called Xeomin, it is designed with only

the active ingredients you need to smooth your frown lines,

and I'm happy with the results.

To finish it up, we do a moisturizer

and then an eye de puffer.

[gentle instrumental music]

Well, there you have it,

my skincare routine.

I hope you took notes, kind of move fast.

Time for the show.

[upbeat music]

Well, it's a beautiful night out, Vogue.

I had a great sign with you, but it's time for the show.

So see you next time.

[gentle instrumental music]
